4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT GENERALLY REVISING LAWS RELATING TO AGRICULTURAL
5 EQUIPMENT AND THE RIGHT TO REPAIR; CREATING THE MONTANA AGRICULTURAL EQUIPMENT
6 REPAIR BILL OF RIGHTS ACT; PROVIDING DEFINITIONS; APPLYING THE ACT TO AGRICULTURAL
7 EQUIPMENT MANUFACTURERS; PROVIDING EXCEPTIONS; AND PROVIDING A DELAYED EFFECTIVE
8 DATE AND A CONTINGENT TERMINATION DATE.”
9
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
11
12 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Short title. [Sections 1 through 4] may be cited as the "Montana
13 Agricultural Equipment Repair Bill of Rights Act".
14
15 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Definitions. For the purposes of [sections 1 through 4], the following
16 definitions apply:
17 (1) (a) "Agricultural equipment" or "equipment" means products used in agriculture, horticulture,
18 and viticulture, dairy products, livestock and the products of livestock, the products of poultry, bee raising, and
19 forestry, products used in property maintenance, and any products raised or produced on farms and processed
20 or manufactured products of products raised or produced on farms that are transported or intended to be
21 transported in interstate or foreign commerce.
22 (b) The term does not include:
23 (i) a motor vehicle that is designed to transport individuals or property on a street or highway and
24 is certified by a motor vehicle manufacturer under all requirements for the distribution and sale of motor
25 vehicles in the United States; or
26 (ii) industrial, construction, compact construction, mining, or road building equipment.
27 (2) "Authorized repair provider" means an individual or business who has an arrangement with the
28 original equipment manufacturer under which the original equipment manufacturer grants to the individual or
