1 business a license to use a trade name, service mark, or other proprietary identifiers for the purposes of
2 offering the services of diagnosis, maintenance, or repair of agricultural equipment under the name of the
3 original equipment manufacturer, or other arrangement with the original equipment manufacturer to offer the
4 services on behalf of, or under contract to, the original equipment manufacturer. An original equipment
5 manufacturer who offers the services of diagnosis, maintenance, or repair of its own agricultural equipment is
6 considered an authorized repair provider with respect to the equipment.
7 (3) "Documentation" means any manual, maintenance procedures, functional and wiring diagrams,
8 reporting output, service code description, board view file or complete PCB layout, PCB schematic, security
9 code, password, training material, troubleshooting information, full list of required tools, full parts list, and other
10 guidance or information used in effecting the services of diagnosis, maintenance, or repair of agricultural
11 equipment.
12 (4) "Fair and reasonable terms" means all of the following:
13 (a) with respect to parts, made available by the original equipment manufacturer, either directly or
14 through an authorized repair provider, in a manner that:
15 (i) is not conditioned on or imposing a substantial obligation or restriction that is not reasonably
16 necessary for enabling the owner or independent repair provider to engage in the diagnosis, maintenance, or
17 repair of agricultural equipment made by or on behalf of the original equipment manufacturer;
18 (ii) does not require a minimum or maximum quantity of parts that owners and independent repair
19 providers can purchase; and
20 (iii) does not condition access to parts on any additional contract other than a purchase order;
21 (b) with respect to documentation, made available by the original equipment manufacturer without
22 requiring any contract agreement or account creation and at no charge except that, when the documentation is
23 requested in physical printed form, a charge may be included for the reasonable actual costs of preparing and
24 sending the copy; and
25 (c) with respect to tools, made available by the original equipment manufacturer:
26 (i) at no charge, except that, when a tool is requested in physical form, a charge may be included
27 for the reasonable actual costs of preparing and sending the tool;
28 (ii) without requiring authorization or internet access for the use or operation of the tools, or
