1 imposing impediments to access or use the tools to diagnose, maintain, or repair and enable full functionality of
2 agricultural equipment; and
3 (iii) in a manner that does not impair the efficient and cost-effective performance of any diagnosis,
4 maintenance, or repair.
5 (5) "Independent repair provider" means an individual or business operating in the state that does
6 not have an arrangement described in subsection (2) with an original equipment manufacturer and who is
7 engaged in the services of diagnosis, maintenance, or repair of agricultural equipment.
8 (6) "Original equipment manufacturer" or "manufacturer" means a business engaged in the
9 business of selling, leasing, or otherwise supplying new agricultural equipment manufactured by or on behalf of
10 itself to an individual or business.
11 (7) "Owner" means an individual or business who owns or leases agricultural equipment
12 purchased or used in this state.
13 (8) "Part" means a replacement part, either new or used, made available or used by an original
14 equipment manufacturer or its authorized repair providers for the purposes of effecting the services of
15 maintenance or repair of agricultural equipment manufactured by or on behalf of, sold, or otherwise supplied by
16 the original equipment manufacturer.
17 (9) "Parts pairing" refers to the practice by manufacturers of using software to identify component
18 parts through a unique identifier.
19 (10) "Tool" means any software program, hardware implement, or other apparatus used for the
20 diagnosis, maintenance, or repair of agricultural equipment, including software or other mechanisms that
21 provision, program, or pair a new part, calibrate functionality, or perform any other function required to bring the
22 product back to fully functional condition, including any updates.
23 (11) "Trade secret" has the meaning provided in 30-14-402.
24 (12) "Updates" means recommended corrections or adjustments to parts, tools, or information that
25 are created and distributed by the original equipment manufacturer and used in offering the services of
26 diagnosis, maintenance, or repair of agricultural equipment.
