1 exemptions. (1) For agricultural equipment and parts for the equipment that are sold or used in the state, an
2 original equipment manufacturer shall make available to any independent repair provider and owner of
3 agricultural equipment manufactured by, on behalf of, or sold by the original equipment manufacturer, on fair
4 and reasonable terms, any documentation, parts, and tools required for the diagnosis, maintenance, or repair of
5 the agricultural equipment and parts for the equipment, inclusive of any updates. The documentation, parts, and
6 tools must be made available either directly by the original equipment manufacturer or through an authorized
7 repair provider or distributor.
8 (2) An original equipment manufacturer may not use parts pairing or any other mechanism to:
9 (a) prevent the installation or functioning of any otherwise functional part, including a
10 nonmanufacturer-approved replacement part or component;
11 (b) inhibit or reduce the functioning of any part or board-level component in such a way that
12 replacement by an independent repair provider or the device owner would cause the device to operate with
13 reduced functionality or performance;
14 (c) create false, misleading, deceptive, or nondismissable alerts or warnings about parts;
15 (d) charge additional fees or increased prices for future repairs; or
16 (e) limit who can purchase documentation, parts, and tools or perform repair services.
17 (3) For equipment that requires deactivating an electronic lock for the purposes of repair, the
18 original equipment manufacturer shall make available to any owner or independent repair provider, with the
19 express permission of the owner, on fair and reasonable terms, any special documentation, tools, and parts
20 needed to access and reset the lock or function when disabled in the course of the diagnosis, maintenance, or
21 repair of the equipment. The documentation, tools, and parts may be made available through an appropriate
22 secure release system.
23
24 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Limitations. (1) Nothing in [sections 1 through 4] may be construed to:
25 (a) require an original equipment manufacturer to divulge a trade secret to an owner or
26 independent service provider, except as necessary to perform the diagnosis, maintenance, or repair on fair and
27 reasonable terms; or
28 (b) alter the terms of an arrangement described in [section 3(1)] in force between an authorized
